# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Versant Forge — environment variables
# Copy to .env.local for local dev. In Vercel, set under Settings > Environment
# Variables (Production / Preview / Development).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Portal surface: which products and nav links to show, and which routes to block
#   full     — default: internal + client surfaces (e.g. changelog) where configured
#   client   — client-facing: hides internal-only links; blocks /changelog
#   internal — reserved for a future internal-only build (same as full for now)
NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_AUDIENCE=full

# Login session — shared password + signing secret. Both are required in any
# environment that should require sign-in.
# PASSWORD=your-shared-password
# FORGE_AUTH_SECRET=openssl-rand-hex-32

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Postgres — Assess product persistence (Neon / Supabase / Vercel Postgres).
# Run `npm run db:migrate` after setting this.
# To migrate against another DB while .env.local stays on dev (PowerShell):
#   $env:MIGRATE_DATABASE_URL = "postgresql://..."; npm run db:migrate; Remove-Item Env:MIGRATE_DATABASE_URL
# Use POSTGRES_URL if you provisioned via the Vercel/Neon template; either works.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@host-pooler.region.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require
# POSTGRES_URL=...

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OpenAI — single global config used by every LLM call site
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Every Versant LLM call (Step 1 dial inference, Step 2 L5 generation,
# Step 4 initiative curation, Step 5 brief authoring, Cross-Tower plan,
# Offshore plan, Ask Forge) routes through src/lib/llm/prompts/versantPromptKit.ts
# and uses ONE model. There are no longer per-feature OPENAI_*_MODEL env vars.
#
# Resolution order for the model id:
#   1. options.model in code (test injection only)
#   2. process.env.OPENAI_MODEL
#   3. built-in default `gpt-5.5` (VERSANT_DEFAULT_MODEL)
#
# Required:
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-...
#
# Optional — global model override. Leave unset to use the default `gpt-5.5`.
# Use this to flip every Versant route to a different model in a single edit
# (e.g. for Vercel Preview environments, or a temporary fallback to `gpt-4o`
# while debugging Responses API issues).
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-5.5
#
# Optional — emergency switch. When `1`, every Versant caller uses Chat
# Completions instead of the Responses API, even on GPT-5 / o-series models.
# Use only if Responses API has an outage.
# OPENAI_FORCE_CHAT_COMPLETIONS=0
#
# Optional — base URL override for OpenAI-compatible endpoints (Azure OpenAI
# proxy, internal gateway, etc). Defaults to https://api.openai.com.
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com
#
# When OPENAI_API_KEY is unset, every LLM-backed feature silently falls back
# to its deterministic Versant heuristic / composer — the program never
# breaks, but the AI-authored content is replaced with deterministic copy.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Notes on legacy env vars (REMOVED in 2026-05 — safe to delete in Vercel)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The following per-feature model overrides are no longer honored anywhere
# in the codebase. They are listed here only so you know what to delete from
# any old Vercel project that still has them set. Setting them now is a no-op.
#
#   OPENAI_INFER_DEFAULTS_MODEL
#   OPENAI_GENERATE_L4_MODEL
#   OPENAI_CURATE_INITIATIVES_MODEL
#   OPENAI_CURATE_BRIEF_MODEL
#   OPENAI_CURATE_BRIEF_REASONING_EFFORT
#   OPENAI_CURATE_BRIEF_USE_CHAT_COMPLETIONS
#   OPENAI_CURATE_BRIEF_MAX_OUTPUT_TOKENS
#   CURATE_BRIEF_TIMEOUT_MS
#   CROSS_TOWER_PLAN_MODEL
#   CROSS_TOWER_PLAN_REASONING_EFFORT
#   CROSS_TOWER_PLAN_TEMPERATURE
#   CROSS_TOWER_PLAN_MAX_TOKENS
#   CROSS_TOWER_PLAN_TIMEOUT_MS
#   CROSS_TOWER_PLAN_CACHE_TTL_S
#   CROSS_TOWER_PLAN_USE_CHAT_COMPLETIONS
#   OPENAI_ASK_MODEL
#   OPENAI_ASK_REASONING_EFFORT
#   OPENAI_ASK_TIMEOUT_MS
#   OPENAI_ASK_USE_CHAT_COMPLETIONS
